caption:
The difference between 93 and E85 on these things will never not impress me. 

The only ‘sort of’ difference between these 2 runs is that we put ice in the tank for the last run on E85, which net’d us about a 20 HP gain. 

So even if we were to compare iced to iced, we’re still talking over a 100 HP improvement from fuel quality alone. 

I blame GM’s piston design. People have their opinions, but this one is mine. The reason why I think it’s the pistons is because these cars run relatively fine on 93 with aftermarket pistons. I believe the sharp spots around the injector cups create hot spots which lead to detonation. 

I’m making a point of posting this because I find it to be more industry knowledge, than common knowledge, still with this platform…. And I honestly get tired of explaining why I suggest a 10k dollar fuel system anytime someone wants to upgrade their LT1/4’s to this power level and beyond. 😂😂

*And I’m not talking about upgrading the DI injectors or HPFP’s* which are ridiculously expensive and have a high failure/problem rate. 

It’s port injection for everything we do over here!

DSX Atlas FTW 💪🏼
